cost_list = [1.0, float('nan'), 2.0, float('nan'), -1.0]
interface = CostListInterface(cost_list)
controller = mlc.create_controller(interface, max_num_runs=10, target_cost=
    -1, max_num_runs_without_better_params=4)
controller.optimize()
self.assertTrue(controller.best_cost == -1.0)
for x, y in zip(controller.in_costs, cost_list):
    self.assertTrue(x == y or math.isnan(x) and math.isnan(y))
